{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/gallstones/diagnosis/diagnostic-tests/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"6a53b54e-76cd-5728-8c33-5775a0b39236","slug":"diagnostic-tests","fullItemName":"Diagnostic tests","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field e2f76517-7179-43f4-a44d-2908f9e422c4 --><h2>What diagnostic tests should I arrange for a person with suspected gallstone disease?</h2><!-- end field e2f76517-7179-43f4-a44d-2908f9e422c4 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item cc54ef44-6e0e-4b02-96a7-b8c11cc28d7f --><!-- begin field 313eef8d-e5e8-4ef9-8932-061971cc3179 --><ul><li><strong>If gallstone disease is suspected in primary care, </strong><strong>or people with abdominal or gastrointestinal symptoms have been unresponsive to previous management, offer: </strong><ul><li>An abdominal ultrasound examination — this may confirm the presence of one or more gallstones.<ul><li>The absence of stones on ultrasound scan does not exclude their existence. </li></ul></li><li>Liver function tests (LFTs) — gallstones in the common bile duct may result in abnormal LFTs.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Consider referral for further investigation if results are normal but clinical suspicion remains high. </strong>This may include: <ul><li>Magnetic resonance cholangiopancreatography (MRCP), if ultrasound has not detected common bile duct stones, but the:<ul><li>Bile duct is dilated and/or</li><li>Liver function test results are abnormal.</li></ul></li><li>Endoscopic ultrasound (EUS) if MRCP does not allow a diagnosis to be made.</li></ul></li><li>Refer people for further investigations if conditions other than gallstone disease are suspected.</li></ul><!-- end field 313eef8d-e5e8-4ef9-8932-061971cc3179 --><!-- end item cc54ef44-6e0e-4b02-96a7-b8c11cc28d7f -->","topic":{"id":"b39f129d-317e-5f6f-8d43-a4b23ddcb2e8","topicId":"b66a5697-882a-4143-a0c6-32b03657c794","topicName":"Gallstones","slug":"gallstones","lastRevised":"Last revised in June 2019","chapters":[{"id":"06a059af-2d68-5ae7-8e88-57f00c6cdb2f","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e0f409fd-998f-5b21-9f3a-5f11ad52d70f","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9db03e94-e4f9-5d18-bd20-c911b8c565e7","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"83aa8167-37ee-5580-b667-eeed0c3c6864","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"e4b85e87-e2a9-57ce-846e-56d02c965e49","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"646754ea-ab1a-5659-bc5e-90394d1f97b8","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"c619902d-f978-51b5-809a-8b8236aefac7","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"5d3a306f-2228-5592-8a4e-035ea7b6849c","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"6070d034-6424-5a50-bc71-08f38595f3f0","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"5a16b326-1085-51b8-ae96-a5dc6abc6057","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"23d93c7f-b7c8-5cb8-9b89-a830fd26ebeb","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"6ba0df39-ebe7-56ba-9f99-dac753d01334","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"8bd75f7e-fefc-54b5-be6f-d430c0236d31","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"e3ba4382-5956-5166-bb69-18323a48c241","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"ffdb00d1-09f5-52b3-8e1f-88dce54b7b9d","slug":"causes-types","fullItemName":"Causes/types"},{"id":"8f6e2df0-5461-54c6-96d4-664988a603e2","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"e0e39604-8c24-5a55-938c-3ae59365b54b","slug":"risk-factors","fullItemName":"Risk factors"},{"id":"2d54fa2b-9f4f-5ef5-a029-42b767680e23","slug":"compl